flowchart TB
    N1["1. neo-zkvm-guest: N4 zk guest"]
    N2["2. L1/native verification: L1 consumes only commitments, messages, or proof results that can be checked."]
    N3["3. L2 execution: L2 owns transaction execution, state advancement, VM profiles, and batch boundaries."]
    N4["4. NeoFS DA: NeoFS stores batch data, witness or trace summaries, and retrievable evidence."]
    N5["5. Proof system: The proof system compresses L2 execution claims into verifiable evidence."]
    N6["6. Gateway/API: Gateway handles user routing, queries, submission, and health aggregation."]
    N7["7. Bridge and heterogeneous chains: Bridge rules unify L1-L2, L2-L2, and heterogeneous-chain messages and assets."]
    N8["8. Developer entry: SDKs, CLIs, templates, and examples expose the system as a usable experience."]
    N1 --> N2
    N1 --> N3
    N1 --> N4
    N1 --> N5
    N1 --> N6
    N1 --> N7
    N1 --> N8
    N2 -. constrains .-> N4
    N4 -. produces .-> N5
    N5 -. consumed by .-> N6
